Profile?language=EN>Tzaroth FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/7/02 12:14:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2498.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Advice</span><hr size=1> As of today, I succeeded in convincing a friend of mine to pick up the EQ Trilogy, and he has since started a Human Paladin. Because he is new, and, obviously, because he's my friend, we have come to the conclusion that we should probably play together at least until we reach the end of the lowbie stage.<br>
<br>
I'm using this as an opportunity to finally squelch my indecisiveness when it comes to characters (I think I've tried almost every combination out there); I'd like to know what classes complement Paladins even averagely in battle. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utaldaydarfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taldaydar FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/7/02 12:20:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2498.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice</span><hr size=1> You really want a healer for a tank/healer duo i suspect. Particularily if your friend is new to eq, makes it alot easier for him/her if there is a healer to keep them from getting killed every 30mins.<br>
<br>
If you intend on playing the duo together to the higher end of the game I would recommend a cleric as being your healer char. If you are not so keen to hit the higher levels then perhaps a druid or a shaman could make a nice partner to the palidin.<br>
<br>
*shrugs*<br>
<br>
Tald. 52 Cleric &amp;&amp; 46 Warrior<br>
