<br>
I've worked with a lot of paladins, and it's always worked out well.  Their spells complement each other, rather than overlapping, in many cases.  A Cleric might make the Paladin, especially if he's new, feel like his spell abilities are just useless.  For every spell he could cast, the Cleric can cast better. <p><center><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~andersonrob/lasgalensig.jpg" border="0"></center>
<b><center>Lasgalen Lothir</center></b>
<i><center>Oakheart of the Conclave of the Righteous</center></i>
<i><center>Warden of Tunare</center></i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umosushi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mosushi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 354<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/7/02 4:08:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2498.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I'd advise ..</span><hr size=1> .. shaman.  I hear they're going to change the name of Firiona-Vie to Druidville.  Shaman are, imho, the very best class for general utility.  You can solo (small) dragons at 60.  You can group with anyone.  You are critical for many high end fights (can't be done without a shaman).  The only reason clerics are higher on the want list for end-game guilds is that you need a lot of them.  A couple shaman go a long way.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Mosushi, Lizard Master of the Fish<br>
<i>"I will gladly pay you Tuesday for Sushi today!"</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uralkorravenblood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ralkor Ravenblood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/7/02 5:38:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2498.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'd advise ..</span><hr size=1> This is the roleplaying server, after all. So why not choose something that has the same or similar morals and goals. <br>
<br>
Maybe you are a cleric serving the same god as your paladin friend, having known him since you were children. And now, having both finished your training at the temple, are eager to wander Norrath and smash evil. <br>
<br>
Of course, there are a variety of choices. A human wizard friend you know from various drinking bou.. err cultivated evenings at the local pub, or almost anything else could work, too. The most important thing to keep in sight, in my opinion, is: What class will you have fun playing? Because when you have fun, your friend will, too. <p><img src=http://eqsighost.netfirms.com/Ralkor/ral.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallerianwintermyst.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vallerian Wintermyst</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/7/02 11:18:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2498.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice</span><hr size=1> I have some good experience with these combinations:<br>
<br>
1). A Mage is a devestating addition to any partner except a rogue. With the mage you get an additional tank, good nuke damage, summoning of anything to keep you in the field indefinitely, and they can heal you with bandages to half and you heal the rest to keep down time very low.<br>
<br>
2). Enchanter. With the enchanter you get an additional tank (more like a DoT that cannot take many hits, but damage non-the-less), good buff and debuffs, haste and slow, the best crowd controller, charming of NPCs in a tough battle, mana regen, and illusions to get the things you need from foreign cities.<br>
<br>
3). Shaman. With the shaman you get a temporary fighter (they can actually fight for a limited time and later they will get a pet), the best melee buffs, the best melee debuffs, healing, health regen, SoW, some devestating DoTs that can really help in a long fight, and some utility spells for vision and charisma for those dark nights and not-so-friendly NPC's.<br>
<br>
Game mechanics-wise, any of these would make a really good companion to a Paladin, but Role-playing-wise choose whatever you want just so long as you both have a good story and are having a great time!<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>--Val

