<lj user=peacefulchaos> !</p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulexxiclockwork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lexxi Clockwork</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 262<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/7/02 11:50:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2498.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Advice</span><hr size=1>      Druid or shaman would complement the abilities of a paladin very well. Since a paladin is limited to an extent on damage dealing except against undead, either of these 2 would help the damage output and between the paladin and their partner the healing would be enough. Do not choose a cleric though, hard to fight anything but undead. Also makes for long fights.<br>
